An oil pipeline breach spilled up to 50,000 gallons of oil into the Yellowstone River near Glendive, Montana.

But the spill, which occurred at 10 a.m. on Saturday, does not pose a threat to public safety or health, according to Montana officials. 

And while some of the oil did get into the water, the area where it spilled was frozen over and that could help reduce the impact, said Dave Parker, a spokesman for Governor Steve Bullock.

