Parker said: 'We think it was caught pretty quick, and it was shut down. The governor is committed to making sure the river is cleaned up.'

Bridger Pipeline Company said in the statement that it shut down the 12-inch-wide pipeline shortly before 11 a.m. Saturday. 

Tad True, vice president of Bridger said: 'Our primary concern is to minimize the environmental impact of the release and keep our responders safe as we clean up from this unfortunate incident.'

